T.O.C.
======

 1.   GBS Builds
 1.1. NON-SMACK Targets
 1.2. SMACK enabled Targets
 2.   Building for Ubuntu desktop
 2.1. Building the repository



1. GBS Builds
=============

1.1. NON-SMACK Targets
----------------------

 gbs build -A [TARGET_ARCH]

1.2. SMACK enabled Targets
--------------------------

 gbs build -A [TARGET_ARCH] --define "%enable_dali_smack_rules 1"



2. Building for Ubuntu desktop
==============================

To build for target first create a dali-env folder in your home golder with:
 dali-core/build/dali_env -c

Then save the environment variables to a file:
 dali-env/opt/bin/dali_env -s > setenv

Next source these variables:
 . setenv

This process only need to be done once.

2.1. Building the repository
----------------------------

To build the repository enter the 'build/tizen' folder:

 cd dali-core/build/tizen

Then run the following commands:

 autoreconf --install
 CXXFLAGS="-g -O0 -Wno-unused-local-typedefs" CXX="ccache g++" ./configure --prefix=$DESKTOP_PREFIX --enable-debug=yes --enable-profile=UBUNTU --enable-gles=20
 make install -j8

